description:
&lt;p&gt;Nurse Hysteroscopist&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Band 7&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hours- negotiable (up to 37.5 hours per week)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting opportunity to come and join the outpatient hysteroscopy team within the gynaecology outpatients department at The Mid Yorkshire Hospitals NHS Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking to recruit a qualified nurse hysteroscopist to join the team and undertake diagnostic outpatient hysteroscopy for an allocated case load of patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role of the nurse hysteroscopist within the department is valued and well established. The successful candidate will work with and be supported by a multidisciplinary team and they will be encouraged to utilise and develop their skills and experience to provide excellent patient experience and participate in service improvement within the hysteroscopy service&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As an experienced gynaecology nurse it is expected you will have extensive theoretical and practical knowledge and have completed the post graduate certification in outpatient hysteroscopy&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicant will be joining a dynamic team that is passionate about women&#39;s health and embraces innovative ways of working .You will be supported and encouraged in your own personal development and will be pivotal to the ongoing development of the service and the role&lt;/p&gt;
